The Chairman League Management Committee of the Nigeria Volleyball Federation (NVBF), Professor Tunde Morakinyo, has announced that the National Division one and two volleyball leagues will commence on June 28 in Ilorin. Morakinyo said that the competition will hold at the indoor/outdoor volleyball court of the University of Ilorin, Kwara State from June 28 to July 5. He said the federation is set to give participating clubs a befitting environment for the tournament.   “The level of preparation ahead of the competition is very high, we are having combination of division one and two together at the same time and the same venue at the university of Ilorin,” he said.